{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C. Grease a rectangular fluted tart tin (21 x 30 cm) and set aside.","Place almonds into mixing bowl and mill <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add all remaining ingredients and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Transfer pastry into prepared tin and press into shape. Using a fork, prick 3-4 times to prevent air bubbles from forming, then place into freezer to rest for 15 minutes.","Bake for 5-8 minutes (200°C) or until lightly golden (see Tips). Remove from oven and leave to cool slightly. Fill pastry case with your desired filling and continue to bake as required."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["110 g coconut oil, plus extra for greasing","150 g blanched almonds","70 g coconut flour","60 g arrowroot starch","40 g coconut sugar","2 eggs"]}],"id":"r99299","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-QTGCcKIpb08\/XZWqv9uMUuI\/AAAAAAAAfcs\/fIYznSe2_48F3ynjn-mmo86-biYjiTn0QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_TS0qduYOjhT-SbPq.png","title":"Sweet shortcrust pastry","publishedAt":"2016-04-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.061 g","fat":"24.927 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"10.668 g","calories":"1197 kJ \/ 285 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rectangular fluted tart tin (21 x 30 cm), oven, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["If your pastry requires no further baking once filled, then continue to bake for a further 2-5 minutes (200°C) in step 5 until pastry is golden brown.","Pastry can be made and baked the day before using. Fill with desired filling and bake or refrigerate prior to serving.","Pastry will fit into a large round tart tin (28 cm) or two smaller tart tins (18 cm).","Pastry can be frozen after step 3. Before using in step 4, defrost completely at room temperature (approx. 4 hours) and press into tart tin and proceed as per recipe.","For best results, pastry needs to be baked and consumed within 2 days of making."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","10 portions"]}